From: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 00:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] amplifiers: cs40l26: pin the codec MFD child platform id
 to 0

The cs40l26-codec MFD child is added with PLATFORM_DEVID_AUTO, so its
device (and thus ASoC component) name depends on the global auto-id
allocation order: "cs40l26-codec.2.auto" on stock WearOS, something
else with our module set/load order. monaco's haptics dai_links must
reference that component by literal name (the aurora DT's
asoc-codec-names/of_node path resolves to a poisoned bolero-spawned
duplicate instead -- see the monaco dailink patch), so the name has
to be deterministic.

Pin the id to 0: the child is always "cs40l26-codec.0". A fixed id
also avoids colliding with the bare "cs40l26-codec" platform device
bolero_add_child_devices() creates from the DT node of the same name.

Applies on top of the loaded-before-mfd-add reorder patch.

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [aurora-specific HW glue]

Signed-off-by: Florent Revest <revestflo@gmail.com>
---
 private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c b/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c
--- a/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c
+++ b/private/google-modules/amplifiers/cs40l26/cs40l26.c
@@ -4952,7 +4952,7 @@ int cs40l26_probe(struct cs40l26_private *cs40l26,

 	cs40l26_loaded = true;

-	ret = devm_mfd_add_devices(dev, PLATFORM_DEVID_AUTO, cs40l26_devs,
+	ret = devm_mfd_add_devices(dev, 0, cs40l26_devs,
 			CS40L26_NUM_MFD_DEVS, NULL, 0, NULL);
 	if (ret) {
 		dev_err(dev, "Failed to register codec component\n");
